node.text:
FIX YOUR FORM: PUSH UPS ❌✅

PLEASE SAVE + RE-SHARE 🙏🏼🙏🏼

Push ups are a VERY common exercise. Its  body weight only and can be done in some variation regardless of your fitness experience level.

As a coach, I do see a lot of people struggle with them…and a lot of the time I think it’s because they aren’t actually sure what a proper push up should look like!

Here are some common issues and then how it’s corrected.

COMMON MISTAKES

❌HEAD LEADING THE MOVEMENT
❌HANDS TOO FAR FORWARD. When you are in position they should be directly under your shoulders.
❌HIPS TOO HIGH/TOO LOW. This puts unnecessary strain on your lower back. You aren’t using your core here to stabilise your body.
❌HANDS TOO WIDE. This limits your range of motion.
❌ELBOWS FLARED. Elbows should not be pointing directly out to the sides. This is putting strain on your shoulders and not putting your chest in proper alignment to work the muscles you want to be!

FORM TIPS:

✅ELBOWS TUCKED IN SLIGHTLY - AT A 45 DEGREE ANGLE
✅HINGE FROM KNEES (NOT HIPS)
✅HANDS SLIGHTLY WIDER THAN SHOULDER-WIDTH APART.
✅HEAD IN LINE WITH BODY. Maintain alignment with your spine.
✅CORE ENGAGED
✅HIPS DOWN

From a kneeling push up - you can progress to doing them up on your toes.🏆

How many can you do?

I hope this was helpful. ❤️ LET ME KNOW! 🙏🏼

GYM HACK: NO BACK EXTENSION MACHINE? TRY THIS!💡💥🤯

I’ve posted this set up hack previously but it was the first time for me doing it at home so thought I’d film and share again!! 👏🏼

Back extensions are one of my favourite for glutes! If your gym doesn’t have the machine try this simple set up using a squat rack, plates & bar pad.

The plates behind your feet will ensure you don’t slip. The pad on the bar will help cushion your hips.

Tip: when doing back extension focus on driving your hips back as you lower down. Initiate the movement from your hips and push your butt back. You should feel this deep in your glute-ham tie in area.

Please let me know if this hack was helpful! ❤️

UNDERRATED COACHING CUES 🎯🔥 Changing the game with your technique! 💡

When you gain more confidence in the gym and movements become more like second nature, there are less cues you feel you need to focus on. I usually pick just 1 or 2 each set.

Think of cues like your checklist. 📝

Here are some of my absolute favourites:

⭐️PUSH THE THE FLOOR AWAY or ‘leg press the floor away’. 

With a deadlift often we think about pulling the weight but if you think about ‘pushing’ the floor away from the starting position you create more force output from your lower body. Your legs are so powerful...so use them!!!
Tension from the ground up!

⭐️DRIVE ELBOWS DOWN TO FLOOR.

Pull yourself up (body to bar) by imagining you are driving your elbows down to the floor. Keep your elbows close to your body and not flared out wide. 

⭐️ROW DUMBBELL TO HIP

Lead the dumbbell with your elbow pulling it back to your hip. Keep your elbow close to your side and torso relatively still. You don’t want to be pulling up to your chest. Bring it back to your hip.

⭐️DRAW BELLY BUTTON TO SPINE & ‘DOUBLE CRUNCH’

Belly button to spine is ensuring your core is engaged and tight. To crunch, you should first initiate the movement with your lower abs tucking under and then rolling your spine from there - kinda like a ‘double crunch’.

These have all been absolute game changers for me! I hope they help you too 🤓🎯

OVERATE THIS WEEKEND? 🍪🍫🍿Did you have a high calorie meal or untracked meal on the weekend and now instantly scared of weight gain?
 
I used to be terrified to eat out or eat an off plan meal because I thought I’d wake up 10kg heavier.

💡TRUTH IS: When you do overeat, you may notice some initial temporary changes to your body. This could be bloating, puffiness, water retention etc…it’s just your bodies natural response to perhaps different types of foods you had consumed and also the extra energy it’s now digesting. As a result - yes your weight may temporarily fluctuate.

Significant fat gain doesn’t just happen over night. 1 untracked meal doesn’t make you fat…just like 1 healthy meal doesn’t make you shredded. Eating in a calorie surplus  consistently is what leads to fat gain.‼️

If you are waking up on a Monday morning feeling bloated and puffy after your weekends food /drink - please be kind to yourself. You are not a failure. It’s a new day and you can always get back to your normal routine of meals and I promise after a couple of days you will feel better!

Get your body moving. Get back to your usual meals. Wear your  favourite comfortable clothes.

There is so much more to life than restricting calories, being anxious about enjoying your favourite foods out with loved ones and punishing yourself as a result.

Be kind to yourself on this Monday honeys 💕✨

I haven’t been posting as many full workouts anymore so take advantage of it when I do. 🙏🏼

This workout is primarily shoulders with a little abs at the end. Remember - if you do want to build and grow your shoulders then you need to train them with frequency, intensity and made sure your exercise selection covers your front, medial and rear delts for that ‘capped’ look.

A1) DB SHOULDER PRESS 3x 10 paused. The pause is at the bottom range here where the exercise is hardest.

A2) LATERAL RAISE 3x 10 paused. The pause is at the top range as that’s where your delts are under the most tension and it’s hardest. I’m doing these seated which also makes the exercise harder as there isn’t any momentum or movement from your legs to assist.

A3) AROUND THE WORLD. 3x 12.

B) Y RAISE 3x 12

C) REAR DELT MACHINE 3x 15. With this exercise - more range of motion is not best! Once your rear delt has fully contracted - anything past this is just going to engage your upper back. Take your arms out directly to the sides & stay within your rear delts active range. 

D1) Hanging alt knee raises 3x 12
D2) Cable crunch 3x 15

node.text:
No food is ‘bad’….. 

Give yourself permission to eat food without fear, guilt or self judgement. Shame and stress are feelings we shouldn’t link with food. 🙏🏼

When you stop completely restricting yourself and actually allow yourself to eat foods you love and enjoy in moderation…you actually don’t crave them or have the urgency to overeat them.
 
Yes - there are some foods that are more nutrient dense than others.

Yes - there are some foods that will be easier on your digestive system, keep you feeling more satiated or just make you feel a whole lot better.

But this doesn’t mean you have to completely cut food groups, starve yourself or eat just chicken and broccoli. 🙅🏼‍♀️

It’s about balance.✅✅✅

Food is not just macros or calories…
Food shouldn’t just be looked at as a numbers game.

Shift your mindset from living with guilt and restriction - too thriving and living life to the fullest.🙏🏼🙋🏼‍♀️❤️

HOME VS GYM 🏡💪🏼 LOWER BODY EDITION.

Please SAVE + TAG a friend who may find this helpful! 🙏🏼 

Showing modifications between gym and home exercises are always some of my most popular and requested posts. I know many of you are still training at HOME right now but I never want you to feel feel disheartened or that you won’t be able to get results - I got you girls👸🏼 

1️⃣ LYING DB + BAND LEG CURL >>>LEG CURL MACHINE. By having both the dumbbell + band you have tension at both the top and bottom of the movement. The dumbbell is hardest at the bottom whereas the band makes it hardest at the top. Challenging your hamstrings in both the lengthened and shortened position. Credit to my boy @coachmarkcarroll for the idea about adding a band to this. 

2️⃣BANDED LEG EXTENSION >>>LEG EXTENSION MACHINE.

Bring knees forward down toward the ground in a squat motion. I do this while up on my toes to further place tension on the quad muscles. Use the band to then extend your legs back and to contract your quads hard.

3️⃣HEELS ELEVATED HACK SQUAT >>>HACK SQUAT MACHINE.

The home variation is using a foam roller behind your back to allow you to move smoothly up and down. You heels should be elevated to increase tension placed on your quads. Make sure your knees track out as you come down into the squat. You can do this holding 2x dumbbells beside you or as I am here in a front racked position. QUAD KILLER!!!!!☠️

4️⃣BAND B-STANCE RDL >>> BB DEADLIFT. I like using different variations of RDL at home with the band. B-stance is my favourite &  using the band is perfect to give you resistance even if you don’t have DBs!

FIX YOUR FORM: LEG PRESS ❌✅

Please SAVE for future reference + RESHARE to support my content.🙏🏼🙏🏼❤️

Firstly, what other exercises did you need a form breakdown on like this?🤔

Leg press is one of my favourite lower body exercises. Depending on your foot placement and positioning you can hit more quads, Glutes/hamstrings, adductors etc.

Common mistakes:

❌Lower back rounding at the bottom
❌Butt lifted off seat
❌Too much depth. When you are using too large a range of motion it’s shifting the tension from your Glutes to your lower back.
❌Knees caving!
❌Forcefully locking out knees at the top of each rep. You are placing a lot of tension on your knee joints which is taking is away from your muscles.

Form tips:

✅Keep slight bend in knees (stop just short of locking them out)
✅Knees track out in line with toes. Consciously think about ‘knees out’ if you find they buckle in under heavy weight.
✅Lower back is flush to the seat. Grab the handles and pull your butt/back down!
✅Staying within range of motion: not too shallow and not too deep.

I hope this was helpful. Let me know! 🙏🏼🤓

How to get your first PULL UP! 🔥READ 👇🏼

When I first started out in the gym a goal of mine was to do 1 unassisted pull up!!! I was once a beginner to and now I can do many!! 🏆

There are stages of progression that can work through:

👉🏼Eccentric only (negatives) pull ups: Here we focus only on the lowering phase. Use a bench to jump up into position & then slowly lower yourself down.

👉🏼Band assisted - around feet.  Assistance by a band in this position allows it to be easier from the bottom. The band is stretched most in this position so has greater ability to assist with each rep.

👉🏼Band assisted - around knees. Having the band around your knees provides less help from the bottom. Try get a few bands of varying thickness so you can decrease the resistance as you get stronger. As you build strength you will be able to lessen the amount of resistance you use until you can do them on your own!!

👉🏼Body weight: Focus on pulling your shoulder blacks back and pulling the bar down with each rep. I imagine pulling my elbows to the floor. If you can only do one rep…try doing 3 sets of one rep. Next week try add an additional rep.

💪🏼Aside from the progression with the actual exercise itself…remember to work on building your overall upper body strength! The stronger you are…the easier and faster your progress will be.

I hope this video helps!! 💗

FIX YOUR FORM: LAT PULLDOWN ❌✅ 

Please SAVE for future reference + RESHARE to support my content. 🙏🏼❤️

When I put up a questions box asking for what you needed help with… upper body exercises technique was high on the request list!

Lat pulldown is a very common upper body exercise targeting your lats/upper back, which for most is ‘basic’ but I still see so many form issues! 🥵

Common mistakes:

❌Putting bar down too low. You don’t need to be pulling down past your chest to your waist. With this exercise more range is not best!
❌Using too much momentum. You don’t need to swing back and use as much momentum to pull the weight. If you want to isolate and engage the right muscles you need strict form.
❌Leaning too far back.
❌Grip too wide. You don’t need to grip all the way at the ends of the bar!

Form tips:

✅Pull bar down to the top of chest/just below chin.
✅Keep forearm as vertical as possible.
✅Drive elbows down
✅Keep chest/torso up with your core braced
✅Use a mid width grip. You should be holding just outside should width.
💪🏼Control the movement

I hope this helped! ✨

What other exercises do you want me to do a breakdown like this for? What exercises do your struggle with the most?

Let me know team!👇🏼👇🏼

DITCH THE BAR PAD WHEN SQUATTING!! 👋🏻

You don’t need it.

🥵Having this cushioned pad around the bar makes it unstable on your back. It’s the same reason why we don’t want to squat in spoungy shoes. You want stability.

🥵The bar sitting off your back just that little bit can throw off your bar path. This will be a lot more noticeable the heavier you squat.

🥵The pad impacts how you can create tightness with your upper back. It’s big and bulky. You won’t be able to pull the bar down tight enough and get your shoulders/elbows into position.

❌ The bar shouldn’t be sitting up too high on your neck, resting on vertebrae. This is what is likely causing pain. 🥵

✅Instead - have the bar sitting a little further down and resting along your traps.

Hold the bar as narrow as you can while squeezing your shoulder blades back tight and then lifting your elbows high (as I show in the video). You also want to keep your chest up.

💡This upper back tightness creates a ‘shelf’ for the bar to rest on. This is your cushion - you don’t need a bar pad. 💪🏼

✨If you are just starting out...squatting for the first time ever and feel more comfortable and confident initially with the pad - that’s okay. Soon enough it will be time to ditch the pad and focus on correct technique so you can progress in weight too! ✨

SAVE THE BAR PAD FOR HIP THRUSTS👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼
